{"RORAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to dew; consisting of dew; dewy.","pos":""}],"RORATION":[{"def":"A falling of dew.","pos":""}],"RORIC":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to dew; resembling dew; dewy.","pos":""}],"RORIFEROUS":[{"def":"generating or producing dew.","pos":""}],"RORIFLUENT":[{"def":"Flowing with dew.","pos":""}],"RORQUAL":[{"def":"A very large North Atlantic whalebone whale (Physalus antiquorum, or Balænoptera physalus).","pos":""}],"RORULENT":[{"def":"Having the surface appearing as if dusty, or covered with fine dew.","pos":""}],"RORY":[{"def":"And shook his wings with rory May-dew wet.","pos":""}]}